# Phase 5 Plan: Presentation Settings

This plan addresses building a highly customizable "Presentation Settings" menu. It will allow the user to modify the appearance of the song lyrics on the live projector screen instantly, similar to OpenSong's presentation layout settings. 

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Settings Data Model & State
#### [NEW] [lib/features/settings/domain/presentation_settings.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/settings/domain/presentation_settings.dart)
- Create a `PresentationSettings` model holding the following properties:
  - `titlePosition` (Top, Bottom, Hidden)
  - `lyricsAlignment` (Left, Center, Right)
  - `backgroundColor` (integer representation of a Flutter Color, e.g., Black, Navy)
  - `fontColor` (integer representation of a Flutter Color, e.g., White, Yellow)
  - `fontFamily` (e.g., Roboto, Arial, Times New Roman)
  - `fontSizeScale` (double, adjusting the base font size for scaling)
  - `padding` (double, configuring screen edges)
- Since you are using **Isar**, we can persist these settings automatically as a singleton record in the Isar database so your preferences remain after app restarts. *For Phase 5, we can focus on getting the Riverpod reactivity working first, or implement the Isar schema right now.*

#### [NEW] [lib/features/settings/presentation/presentation_settings_provider.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/settings/presentation/presentation_settings_provider.dart)
- A Riverpod `NotifierProvider` that manages the active `PresentationSettings`. When updated, it forces the `LiveProjectorPane` to rebuild.

